description:
&lt;p&gt;Employer: Cardiff and Vale University Health Board&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Department: Phlebotomy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: University Hospital Llandough/University Hospital of Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: £17,652 to £19,020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours available:- Full &amp; Part Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff &amp; Vale UHB is looking for a Phlebotomist who is enthusiastic and reliable and shares the organisations values and core beliefs,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We trust one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We respect each other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take personal responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We treat people with kindness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We act with integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of a team you will be required to take blood samples from patients who are hospital in-patients, outpatients and patients at GP Practices. Although experience is desirable, it is not essential as full training will be given. Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate at all levels is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve some travelling between sites within the University Health Board such as University Hospital of Wales, University Hospital Llandough, Barry Hospital, St Davids and many GP Practices so the ability to meet the travel requirements is a prerequisite of this role, and the ability to safely transport laboratory samples is also essential. &lt;strong&gt;Please indicate how you will meet this requirement in your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Saturday &amp; Sunday rota is in place (working 1 in 4 approx) &amp; Bank Holidays on rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospital of Wales and University Hospital Llandough are NO Smoking Hospitals. Please note that there are no smoking facilities for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Ceri Hooper&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Phlebotomy Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: ceri.hooper@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0292048190 &lt;/p&gt;
